To the teams at Eurosport and GCN from the studio floor up, thank you for your commitment and passion. To everyone who chooses social media as a platform for support & encouragement, I applaud you. To everyone who wants to just be themselves, do it. You‚Äôre the only one who can üôè

I do so with a foundation of hard work, professionalism and research and with 4 weeks of Tour de France coverage now done, I could not be more grateful. To everyone who‚Äôs been in touch to say they‚Äôve been more daring in their debates on sport or their choice of clothes, I üíõ you

I have chosen to be entirely me, rather than a telly-fied, societally-approved version of what we‚Äôre told to expect a woman on TV or in sport to be. I have had fun, I have screamed, I have cried, I have danced, worn what I wanted and celebrated as I saw fit.

A few very personal words for anyone who‚Äôs bothered. As a woman in sport I point out the times that I feel othered, objectified or belittled for how I choose to represent, but this past month has empowered and liberated more than I could have hoped

Why I cried today; for the girl I was who had no sporting role models beyond the Olympics, for the girls who get to see now as normal, for all who fought for and celebrated equalityü¶¨ We have turned a corner, turned a page and it feels f*cking good.  https://t.co/VPt6cH06rj
